Description
Directory Traverser is a command line tool in C that list files and directories recurively. Also support filtering by pattern, size, type, and handles symbolic links.

Getting Started
Prerequisites:
C Complier (e.g., GCC)
Unix-based OS or compatible (Linux,macOS,WSL)

Installation:
Clone the respoitory or download the source code
git clone <respoitory url>

Compile the code using the Makefile:
make
make run

Compile the code without using the Makefile:
gcc -o filename filename.c
./filename

